Configure Impacket Tools (secretsdump, smbexec)
Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

Install and configure Impacket tools on a Linux system
Use secretsdump to extract credentials from Windows systems
Execute commands remotely using smbexec
Automate Impacket operations with Python scripts
Understand security implications of credential dumping and remote execution
Prerequisites
Basic Linux command line operations
Understanding of Windows Active Directory concepts
Knowledge of SMB protocol and NTLM authentication
Basic Python programming skills
Familiarity with penetration testing concepts
