Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: Impacket installation fails

Ensure Python 3.6+ is installed
Install build dependencies: sudo apt install python3-dev libssl-dev
Use virtual environment to avoid conflicts
Issue: Connection timeout with smbexec

Verify target is reachable: ping target_ip
Check SMB ports are open: nmap -p 445 target_ip
Ensure credentials are correct
Verify firewall rules allow SMB traffic
Issue: secretsdump returns no results

Confirm you have proper privileges (admin/domain admin)
Check if target has credential caching enabled
Verify SYSTEM and SAM/NTDS files are accessible
Ensure correct file paths are specified
Conclusion
This lab provided hands-on experience with Impacket's secretsdump and smbexec tools. Students learned to extract credentials, execute remote commands, and automate operations using Python. These skills are essential for penetration testing and security assessments, but must be used ethically and legally with proper authorization. The automation framework developed can be extended for additional Impacket tools and integrated into larger security testing workflows.

